From: Bedrock <bedrock@example.com>
Subject: [PATCH 1/3] x86/mm: Force TLB flush on any PTE flag change

For deterministic execution under hypervisors with VPID enabled,
force TLB flush whenever PTE flags change, not just when permissions
are demoted. This prevents spurious faults from stale TLB entries.

Signed-off-by: Bedrock <bedrock@example.com>
---
 arch/x86/include/asm/tlbflush.h | 7 +++++++
 1 file changed, 7 insertions(+)

diff --git a/arch/x86/include/asm/tlbflush.h b/arch/x86/include/asm/tlbflush.h
index abcdef123..1234567ab 100644
--- a/arch/x86/include/asm/tlbflush.h
+++ b/arch/x86/include/asm/tlbflush.h
@@ -417,6 +417,13 @@ static inline bool pte_flags_need_flush(unsigned long oldflags,
  */
 static inline bool pte_needs_flush(pte_t oldpte, pte_t newpte)
 {
+	/*
+	 * Force TLB flush on any flag change for deterministic execution
+	 * under hypervisors with VPID. Avoids spurious faults.
+	 */
+	if (pte_flags(oldpte) != pte_flags(newpte))
+		return true;
+
 	/* !PRESENT -> * ; no need for flush */
 	if (!(pte_flags(oldpte) & _PAGE_PRESENT))
 		return false;
--
